#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn14.34"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn14.34:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 14 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 14 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn14.34:0.2"
msgid "4. Catutthavagga "
msgstr "4. The Fourth Chapter "

# NOTE: BB has suffering for dukkha here. But note that the phrase ekantadukkha usually, probably always in fact, refers to painful feelings.
#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 34. Ekantadukkhasutta → dukkhalaṅkaṇasuttaṃ (bj) | dukkha (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn14.34:0.3"
msgid "34. Ekantadukkhasutta "
msgstr "34. Exclusively Painful "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn14.34:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Pathavīdhātu ce → paṭhavīdhātu ca (bj) | paṭhavīdhātuñca (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn14.34:1.2"
msgid "“Pathavīdhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave, ekantadukkhā abhavissa dukkhānupatitā dukkhāvakkantā anavakkantā sukhena, nayidaṃ sattā pathavīdhātuyā sārajjeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, if the earth element were exclusively painful—soaked and steeped in pain and not steeped in pleasure—sentient beings wouldn’t love it. "

msgctxt "sn14.34:1.3"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātu sukhā sukhānupatitā sukhāvakkantā anavakkantā dukkhena, tasmā sattā pathavīdhātuyā sārajjanti. "
msgstr "But because the earth element is pleasurable—soaked and steeped in pleasure and not steeped in pain—sentient beings do love it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.174, sc2
msgctxt "sn14.34:2.1"
msgid "Āpodhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave … pe … "
msgstr "If the water element … "

msgctxt "sn14.34:2.2"
msgid "tejodhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "If the fire element … "

msgctxt "sn14.34:2.3"
msgid "vāyodhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave, ekantadukkhā abhavissa dukkhānupatitā dukkhāvakkantā anavakkantā sukhena, nayidaṃ sattā vāyodhātuyā sārajjeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "If the air element … "

msgctxt "sn14.34:2.4"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, vāyodhātu sukhā sukhānupatitā sukhāvakkantā anavakkantā dukkhena, tasmā sattā vāyodhātuyā sārajjanti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn14.34:3.1"
msgid "Pathavīdhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave, ekantasukhā abhavissa sukhānupatitā sukhāvakkantā anavakkantā dukkhena, nayidaṃ sattā pathavīdhātuyā nibbindeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "If the earth element were exclusively pleasurable—soaked and steeped in pleasure and not steeped in pain—sentient beings wouldn’t grow disillusioned with it. "

msgctxt "sn14.34:3.2"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātu dukkhā dukkhānupatitā dukkhāvakkantā anavakkantā sukhena, tasmā sattā pathavīdhātuyā nibbindanti. "
msgstr "But because the earth element is painful—soaked and steeped in pain and not steeped in pleasure—sentient beings do grow disillusioned with it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn14.34:4.1"
msgid "Āpodhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave … pe … "
msgstr "If the water element … "

msgctxt "sn14.34:4.2"
msgid "tejodhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "If the fire element … "

msgctxt "sn14.34:4.3"
msgid "vāyodhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave, ekantasukhā abhavissa sukhānupatitā sukhāvakkantā anavakkantā dukkhena, nayidaṃ sattā vāyodhātuyā nibbindeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "If the air element were exclusively pleasurable—soaked and steeped in pleasure and not steeped in pain—sentient beings wouldn’t grow disillusioned with it. "

msgctxt "sn14.34:4.4"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, vāyodhātu dukkhā dukkhānupatitā dukkhāvakkantā anavakkantā sukhena, tasmā sattā vāyodhātuyā nibbindantī”ti. "
msgstr "But because the air element is painful—soaked and steeped in pain and not steeped in pleasure—sentient beings do grow disillusioned with it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn14.34:4.5"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

